The Poject "Visualizing 1946-23 NBA Teams Game" is a data visualization project that uses Tableau to analyze and display the performance of NBA teams from 1946 to 2023. The project aims to provide a comprehensive view of the teams' scores, ELO ratings, year-wise quality of game ans performance. The data is collected from various sources, including historical records and statistics, and is then cleaned and processed to be ready for analysis.

The project starts by analyzing the scores of the teams over time, using line charts and bar charts to display the trend and patterns in the data. The ELO ratings, which are a measure of a team;s strength and performance, are also analyzed and visualized using bar charts and scatter plots. This allows us to see how theteams' performance has evolved over time and how it compares to other teams.
